  <description><![CDATA[<p>Close to Molo Beverello harbour and Castel dell'Ovo, Hotel Rex offers a quiet yet central location in the waterfront district of San Ferdinando. The 20th Century Art Nouveau building has a Mediterranean feel interior and comfortable rooms with an elegant simplicity. The hotel has a calm and relaxing atmosphere away from the buzz and energy of the soulful <a data-udi="umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a1a80922d88a43f8ba80b182c72e8904}" title="Italy">Italian</a> city.</p>
<p>Many of <a data-udi="umb://document/3f78d09ffda249fe84dca900e9fedde9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f78d09ffda249fe84dca900e9fedde9}" title="Naples">Naples'</a> attractions are within walking distance and the hotels's close proximity to transport links makes it simple to hop on a bus or metro if you're looking to go further afield. The nearest bus stop is just 130 metres from the hotel and Municipio Metro stop is about a 15-minute walk away.</p>
<p>We recommend walking along the waterfront towards Piazza del Plebiscito, it's just a ten-minute walk from the hotel and a hub of activity night and day. If you're visiting Naples to taste the authentic Italian cuisine, you’ll find yourself perfectly situated at Hotel Rex. It's near to lots of restaurants and bars so you’ll find it easy to sample the famous wood fired pizzas. After a day of exploring, the hotel's bar is a great spot to enjoy an evening drink or to take a moment to relax.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 25 mins by private car from Naples airport.</p>]]></description>
